        "description": "The insert_is_trie theorem states that inserting an element into a valid trie results in a valid trie. Looking at the definition of is_trie, it is defined simply as True. Therefore, any proposition of the form is_trie X is trivially true. The proof requires no induction or unfolding of the insert operation. We can simply start the proof, ignore the hypotheses, and use the exact I or constructor tactic to discharge the goal. This is a quick win that reduces the Admitted count without complex dependencies.",
